<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece Opposes NATO's Military Intervention in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece once again expressed on
Monday its opposition to a possible military intervention by NATO
in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas said that Greece had serious reservations about
any military action which NATO might conduct in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
While expressing the hope that the consultations currently
under way would yield positive results, he stressed that the
Kosovo crisis must be resolved politically through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
He added that there must be no more bloodshed in the Balkan
region.
</P>
<P>
Greece has repeatedly made it clear that it opposes Kosovo's
independence from Yugoslavia but a broad autonomy should be given
to Kosovo where ethnic Albanians make up 90 percent of its nearly
2 million population and have been demanding independence from
Belgrade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
