<HEADLINE> Wedding on Internet in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen couples of
Singaporeans had their marriage solemnization telecast live on the
Internet, believed to be the first of its kind in the world.
</P>
<P>
Under the joint arrangement by the Registry of Marriages and
the National Computer Board, their wedding ceremonies were
conducted in Chinese and telecast over the Chinese Internet with
the events lasting from mid-morning to afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Before the eyes of hundreds of thousands, the brides and
bridegrooms registered and exchanged their vows with their loved
ones.
</P>
<P>
These couples were among the record 118 couples who timed their
wedding to coincide with the Chinese Mid-Autumn Festival which is
considered one of the most auspicious days to get married.
</P>
<P>
The events were designed to promote the use of Chinese
Internet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
