<HEADLINE> 1 Israeli Soldier Killed in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 5 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli soldier was killed and
four others wounded on Monday in a roadside bomb explosion in
south Lebanon, Lebanon's Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was detonated when an Israeli convoy passed by the
Hasbiyeh village in the eastern sector of the Israeli-occupied
south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The wounded have been taken to a nearby hospital for treatment,
the radio said.
</P>
<P>
No group has claimed responsibility for the bombing.
</P>
<P>
Fifteen Israeli soldiers have been killed and 86 others wounded
in roadside bomb blasts in south Lebanon so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a so-called security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border
attacks by Lebanese Muslim guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon's resistance militants have been fighting to drive the
1,500 Israeli occupation forces out of Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
