<HEADLINE> Woodbridge Ousts Courier in Three-Set Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Australian doubles ace Todd
Woodbridge ousted former world number one Jim Courier of the
United States in the first round of the Shanghai ATP tour on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The eighth-seeded Australian came back from one set down to
beat Courier, who entered the event as wild card, 1-6, 6-3, 7-6
(8-6), in two hours and nine minutes.
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge's doubles pair, Mark Woodforde of Australia, also
advanced to the second round after edging Zimbabwe's Wayne Black
7-6 (7-1), 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Third-seeded American Jan-Michael Gambill struggled to move
into the next round by beating a big challenge from wild card
Zhang Yu of China, winning 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia and second-seeded
Michael Chang of the United States were scheduled to play their
first-round matches on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
