<HEADLINE> Taiwan's Signing of Covenant is illegal, Qin Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese diplomat
said here on Monday that the signature by the Taiwan authorities
to the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights in
1967 is "illegal and null and void."
</P>
<P>
Qin Huasun, Chinese permanent representative to the United
Nations, said that "The signature that the Taiwan authorities
affixed, by usurping the name of 'China,' to the International
Covenant on Civil and Political Rights on October 5, 1967, is
illegal and null and void."
</P>
<P>
Qin made the statement after he signed the Covenant on behalf
of the Chinese Government.
</P>
<P>
There is only One China in the world, the Government of the
People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate representative
of the Chinese people as a whole, and Taiwan is an inalienable
part of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
