<HEADLINE> Greece Blames Turkey for Tense Relations With Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Monday blamed
neighboring Turkey for the recent tension between Turkey and
Syria.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas said that all countries should take steps to
ensure a climate of stability and security in the region, but
Turkey dynamited all attempts at creating such a climate.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for good faith between neighboring
countries, saying that problems should be resolved on the basis of
international law.
</P>
<P>
Tension between Turkey and Syria has reportedly worsened
recently with Syria concerned at Turkey's growing military
relations with Israel and Turkey blaming Syria for backing Kurdish
guerrilla forces.
</P>
<P>
Greece, which has bad ties with Turkey for decades, also
attacks Turkey for its growing military ties with Israel, saying
that this will unbalance the military strengths in the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
