<DOCNO> XIE19981006.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola FM: Togo, Burkina Faso's Aid to UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government has
warned that it would not tolerate Togo and Burkina Faso's support
to Angola's opposition movement the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
Joao Miranda, Deputy Foreign Minister, said at the 53rd
General Assembly of the United Nations Sunday that the fact Togo
and Burkina Faso offer their land for military training of UNITA
men is running against the spirit of the U.N. Charter and the
resolutions of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
"We would warn countries like Togo and Burkina Faso that the
Angolan government would no longer tolerate their support to
UNITA military force under Jonas Savimbi," the Angolan News
Agency Angog Monday quoted Miranda as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Angolan government has recognized the UNITA
Renovation Committee, a splinter group, because it is devoted to
reforming UNITA into a civilian party and willing to carry out
the tasks mapped out by the 1994 Lusaka Peace Protocol.
</P>
<P>
He urged that the whole world should recognize the UNITA
Renovation Committee as the sole representative of UNITA, just
like what the Southern African Development Community (SADC) has
done.
</P>
<P>
It is a cautious and realistic way for the Angolan government
to keep Savimbi, a "war criminal" as termed by the SADC, away
from another chance in the countriy's peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government changed its attitude since September as
UNITA refused to disarm all its men, refused to hand over the
main areas under its control to state administration and began to
attack state-owned areas including cities and towns.
</P>
<P>
It it under this situation that the government severed ties
with Savimbi and took on the UNITA Renovation Committee as the
legal negotiator in future peace talks, in a bid to break the
delok in the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
