<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Leader Calls for Enhanced Family Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi called Monday, at the opening ceremony of an international
conference of women lawyer here, for efforts to enhance role of
families in African societies in the next century.
</P>
<P>
The 29th bi-annual Convention of the International Federation
of Women Lawyers (FIDA) brings together female jurists, judges
and academics from 70 countries to deliberate and exchange views
on various issues affecting women, including family laws.
</P>
<P>
"There is need for all of us to strengthen our traditional
values and preserve the important role of the family unit of
creating a cohesive society," Moi stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, modern technological developments and exposure
to foreign influences have exposed this important social unit to
severe social test," he sighed.
</P>
<P>
"The introduction of a monetary economy has made people
increasingly individualistic -- it is women and children who have
suffered most from these development," said Moi.
</P>
<P>
"The promotion of women's education is crucial toward
enhancing their social economic status as well as that of their
families and the nation," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said his government has invested a considerable amount of
its resources in promoting education nationwide, resulting in the
increase of the percentage enrollment of girls at the primary
school level from 34 percent to 49.3 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
"The (Kenyan) government is determined to put in place
mechanisms to ensure equal access to education opportunities and
to eliminate gender disparities in the provision of education,"
he told women lawyers at the conference.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will go on under the theme of "the Woman of the
21st Century until Thursday in the Kenyan capital.
</P>
<P>
FIDA, founded in Mexico in 1944, is a non-governmental
organization aimed at promoting and defending the rights of women
and children in their legal and social context. The last FIDA
convention was held in Hong Kong in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
