<HEADLINE> Romanian FM Reasserts Peaceful Settlement of Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Romanian Foreign Minister
Andrei Plesu Monday reasserted Romania's stand for a peaceful
settlement of the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
According to the press office of the ministry, Plesu made the
statement when meeting with the chiefs of the diplomatic missions
of the Contact Group member countries in Bucharest at their
request.
</P>
<P>
The foreign diplomats presented to the Romanian Foreign
Minister a report on the Contact Group's diplomatic actions as
regards the Kosovo crisis management and implementation of the
provisions of the U.N.'s Security Council Resolution 1199
demanding the cease of violence in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Plesu stressed on the occasion the political solidarity of
Romanian diplomacy with the Contact Group's actions.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Foreign Minister briefed the diplomats on the results
of his meeting on September 22, in New York, with the Yugoslav
Foreign Minister and their talks over the Kosovo problem. 
</P>
