<HEADLINE> Romanian, Turkish Military Officials on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 5 (Xinhua) -- "Firm ways will be used to
resolve the Kosovo crisis, if the diplomatic one will not be
possible," visiting Chief of Turkish Army's General Staff Huseyin
Kivrikoglu said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Both the U.N. and the NATO "do not want a new Bosnia",
Kivrikoglu said at a press conference held after talks with his
Romanian counterpart Constantin Degeratu.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Romanian Army's General Staff Degeratu said that
Romania was in favor of resolving the crisis by political means in
accordance with the resolutions adopted by the U. N. Security
Council. He considers as a priority the ceasing of conflicts, the
stop of violence and the observance of human rights in the area.
</P>
<P>
Huseyin Kivrikoglu arrived here on Sunday for a three-day
visit. He held talks with Degeratu on various issues, such as the
need to boost direct contacts between the General Staffs of the
two armies, the importance of promoting immediate relations
between chiefs of certain departments within the staffs and means
to cooperate in the troops'training.  
