<HEADLINE> Mozambican Plane Lands Without Injuries After </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- A Boeing 747 passenger plane
belonging to Air Mozambique managed an emergent landing Monday
with no injuries after one of its four engines exploded in
mid-air.
</P>
<P>
It is said that a total of 97 passengers were on the plane
heading for Johannesburg, South Africa when the accident occurred
just 10 minutes after it took off from Maputo International
Airport, Mozambican News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Some citizens in Matola, 10 kilometers away from Maputo,
said they heard the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The crew of the plane are Mozambicans and South Africans.
</P>
<P>
Joao de Abreu, an official with Air Mozambique, said that the
accident is "not very serious", saying accident like this is very
common in the world.
</P>
<P>
He said the plane could not take off at least Monday or today.
And he did not give the reason for the accident.
</P>
<P>
Air Mozambique used a Foker plane to lift passengers to
Johannesburg for fear that passengers might miss their
international flights to other places because of the accident.
</P>
