<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- President Negasso Gidada
said Monday that his Government is committed to preserving the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of Ethiopia and will do
everything to safeguard the nation's sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the first joint meeting of the 4th year working
term of the House of People's Representatives and the House of
Federation, Negasso said the main task facing the government is
the liberation of territory occupied by neighboring Eritrea -- by
force if peace efforts failed.
</P>
<P>
"The Government of Ethiopia still views war as a last resort
to settle interstate disputes and is committed to exhausting all
possible avenues of peace,'' he stated, adding that however, "the
chance for a peaceful resolution of the conflict is dimming by
the day because of the intransigence of the Eritrean regime."
</P>
<P>
The President told the two houses that "we will not allow
anything to sidetrack us from our chosen path of development and
social transformation."
</P>
<P>
speaking about the economy, he said the country will make
headways in the implementation of all socio-economic development
projects.
</P>
<P>
"We have managed to attain self-sufficiency in food production
and there is a good prospect to ensure food security at the
household level," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He further said the other challenges for Ethiopia during the
current year would be to exert efforts to improve the quality and
quantity of the country's cash crops, such as coffee, and to
boost foreign exchange earnings. 
</P>
