<HEADLINE> China, Britain Cooperate In Dealing With Vehicle Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China's State Environmental
Protection Bureau Administration and Britain's Department of Trade
and Industry (DTI) held a conference on environmental protection
and emission controls here today.
</P>
<P>
Specialists in the field from various British universities,
companies, and research institutes spoke about their achievements
in catalytic technology, engine development, and lubrication
technology.
</P>
<P>
The UK has 28 million vehicles in an area little bigger than
Guangdong Province, so environmental issues are very important,
according to Stuart Nunn, Director of International Automotive
Relations at DTI.
</P>
<P>
The British government works in partnership with the automotive
industry and universities on reducing vehicle pollution. He said
that they are delighted to share their experience with their
Chinese friends.
</P>
<P>
A Sino-UK Center of Excellence for Automotive and Environmental
Technologies in Beijing was also announced at a press conference
today.
</P>
<P>
It will focus on environmental protection technology,
specifically that for reducing pollution from buses and commercial
vehicles and to develop technology for industry on a commercial
basis.  
