<HEADLINE> Senior U.S. Official to Mediate Ethio-Eritrean </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Former U.S. National
Security Adviser Anthony Lake will arrive here Thursday to
facilitate a peaceful solution to the current Ethio-Eritrean
conflict.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by the Ethiopian government in a
statement issued here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government pledged its commitment to the
on-going Organization of African Unity (OAU) initiative as the
only one that "could guarantee a peaceful solution to the crisis,
and will welcome any efforts made by other parties to bolster
this initiative," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
"In line with this determination to find a peaceful solution
Ethiopia supported the United States and Rwanda proposals, the
OAU resolution and the U.N. Security Council decision, and
cooperated fully with them in order that peace may prevail," the
statement added.
</P>
<P>
After the border conflict erupted in May, the United States
and Rwanda formulated a proposal which requested withdrawal of
the Eritrean forces from the occupied Badme area near the border.
However, the proposal was refused.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea have squabbled for years over disputed
territory along their border. But the dispute turned violent in
May this year with each side accusing the other of invasion.
