<HEADLINE> Turkey to Give Strict Responses to Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Defense Minister Ismet
Sezgin said Tuesday that Turkey would give very strict responses
to other countries supporting the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK).
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency quoted Sezgin, who is
visiting Izmir city along the Aegean coast, as saying that Turkey
preferred to solve problems with Syria in friendship and in peace
and within reciprocal dialog for years.
</P>
<P>
"Endurance and patience have limits, we say that we have
reached the limit", said the minister.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has massed heavy government troops along the border
with Syria to conduct military exercises, which fueled the
tensions between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Sezgin said that Turkey warned Syria once again to save it
from the danger it is facing, adding that "we used diplomacy
again. We are trying to fulfill the requirements of
diplomacy. Whatever possible will be done if there is no
diplomacy."
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long accused Syria of harboring the PKK, which has
been fighting since 1984 for autonomy for the Kurdish minority in
southeastern Turkey. But Syria denied the charge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
