<HEADLINE> Russia Supports Peaceful Solution to Turkish-Syrian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Moscow has expressed its support
for a peaceful and diplomatic resolution of the Turkish-Syrian
dispute.
</P>
<P>
Russia's position was announced here Tuesday by the country's
Ambassador to Cyprus, Georgi Mouradov, after a meeting with the
leader of the island's ruling Democratic Rally party, Nicos
Anastasiades.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters about his country's stance on the crisis
between Turkey and Syria, Mouradov expressed Moscow's concern
about developments in the region.
</P>
<P>
"We are in favor of a peaceful, diplomatic solution to all
issues between the two states," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Russia "is interested in the stability and peace
in the region, which is very close to its borders".
</P>
<P>
Tensions have been mounting recently between Syria and Turkey
after they traded accusations against each other, and Turkey has
reportedly massed troops along its border with Syria.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has accused Syria of harboring the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK), which has been fighting since 1984 for an
independent Kurdish state in the southeast of Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Syria has lashed out at Turkey for forming a military alliance
with Israel, which it says poses a threat to the Arab world as a
whole, especially itself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
