<HEADLINE> England Pulls Out of Champions' Trophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 6 (Xinhua) -- England has pulled out of the
Champions' Trophy hockey tournament in Lahore, Pakistan, for
security reason, the England Foreign Office confirmed on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Office made the decision because U.S. missile struc
k in August against a suspected guerrilla base in neighbouring
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"No matter how small the risk, we have to put our players,
support staff and supporters first. In that respect, this
decision has been simple," Chris Spice, the England international
performance director, was quoted as saying, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament starts on October 31. 
