<HEADLINE> Chinese Official on Cross-Straits Political Negotiations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Recently some people in Taiwan have said that the two could
have a dialogue and we have seen this as a positive sign," Wang
told participants at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tang Shubei, executive vice-president of ARATS, said that
political negotiations are the only way to effectively protect the
rights and interests of people on both sides of the Taiwan
Straits. "We should never reduce our responsibility of
safeguarding the rights and interests of compatriots on both sides
of the Straits," he said, adding that there are two issues that
are really important to the rights and interests of more than 21
million Taiwan compatriots and some 1.2 billion people on the
mainland.
</P>
<P>
"One is to end hostilities across the Taiwan Straits as soon as
possible, and the other is to have direct postal service, trade
and air and shipping services across the Straits," he said.
