be resolved without use of force through Russia's efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported Yeltsin informed Chirac by
telephone of Russia's latest attempts to ensure a political
settlement of the crisis. (Russia-France-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright said
here Tuesday that there is still much work to be done to push
forward the peace talks between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after her meeting with Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, Albright said that both Israeli and
Palestinian leaders have to make hard decisions to break the
current deadlock over the Israeli troops' second redeployment in
the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived here Tuesday morning in an attempt to narrow
differences between the two sides ahead of a mid-October
Washington three-way summit to try to clinch a deal on the
redeployment. (Israel-Albright-Peace Talks)
</P>
