<HEADLINE> European Conference Calls for Environment Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The second European
Conference called on Tuesday for further cooperation on
environmental protection among the European countries.
</P>
<P>
The conference pointed out that many threats to the environment
respected no frontiers and globalization of the economy had to be
accompanied by globalization of environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The participants agreed that improvement of the environment was
a particularly appropriate area for regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Attending Tuesday's European Conference were the foreign
ministers from European Union (EU) member states, the applicant
countries bidding for EU membership and Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers noted that trans-boundary European
environmental challenges such as air and water pollution and
those resulting from dangerous chemicals, transport, the shipment
of waste, energy and nuclear safety, had to be addressed by all
partners with a maximum of coordination and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection and regional cooperation were two of
the major topics at the inaugural European Conference held in
March this year in London. The first conference was attended by
heads of state and government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
