<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dates of Indo-Pak Official Level Talks Finalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- India and Pakistan Tuesday
finalized the dates for official level talks here on six
outstanding issues between the two countries, official sources
said here.
</P>
<P>
Official level talks will follow foreign secretary level
dialogue between the two countries on peace and security including
confidence building measures and Jammu and Kashmir issue in
Islamabad on October 15.
</P>
<P>
The decision to restart the dialogue stalled since last year
was taken by Indian and Pakistani prime ministers Atal Behari
Vajpayee and Nawaz Sharif when they met in New York on September
23 on the sidelines of the United Nations General Assembly
session.
</P>
<P>
Since the nuclear tests conducted by India and Pakistan in May
this year, the world community has time and again urged the two
South Asian nations to resume their talks.
</P>
<P>
The Indo-Pak official level talks will start from early
November this year. Secretaries of the two countries from
ministries of water and power, defense, commerce, home, culture,
etc. are scheduled to meet from November 5 onwards to discuss
Tulbul navigation project, the Siachen issue, the long pending Sir
Creek boundary dispute, joint measures for combating terrorism and
drug trafficking and to explore prospects of enhancing economic
and commercial cooperation, as well as steps for promotion of
friendly exchanges in various fields, the sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
