<HEADLINE> Journalists Commended for Flood Coverage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- About 100 journalists from the
Xinhua News Agency, People's Daily, and other news media were
singled out and commended today for their outstanding performance
in covering the country's recent fight against the worst floods in
decades.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, the head of the Publicity Department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, told a meeting
at Beijing's Great Hall of the People today that the coverage of
the recent floods by Chinese journalists displayed their political
awareness, sense of responsibility, affection for the people, and
excellent work style.
</P>
<P>
During two months of summer flooding that hit the entire
Yangtze River basin and the Nenjiang and Songhua rivers in the
Northeast, Chinese national news organizations sent over 1,000
journalists to report on the fight and to record the heroic
efforts of civilians and soldiers.
</P>
<P>
"You have written a glorious chapter in our country's
journalistic history," Ding told the group and urged journalists
nationwide to make an effort to reflect the same fighting spirit
that emerged in the battle against the floods and to encourage
people to work harder for this year's reforms and development.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting also recognized the efforts of 33 departments
of news organizations for their major contributions to the flood
work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
