<HEADLINE> Tide-Watching Festival in Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- About 50,000 tourists attended
today's opening ceremony at the 1998 China Qiantang River
Tide-Watching Festival in the city of Haining in China's Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
Watching tidal changes on the Qiantang River at this time of
year has been a tradition for the people of Haining for 800
years. It was turned into an international event in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Ying Zhongliang said that the site has attracted millions
of people from all over the world since 1994 and that he hopes the
festival will promote economic and cultural exchanges and
cooperation with domestic and foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The festival sponsors will host a series of tourist programs
and a leather fashion show during the five-day event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
