<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction Work Begins On East China Reservoir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on the
Gangkouwan Reservoir, the largest water conservation project in
east China's Anhui Province, began today in Ningguo City.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir is being built on the Yangjiang River, a branch
of the Yangtze, and is the first water conservation project to
begin after this summer's serious flooding along the middle and
lower reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
It will cost 1.1 billion yuan and will cover a 1,120 sq. km.
area, with a storage capacity of 941 million cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
It will provide 113 million kwh of electricity by the year
2002.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir will submerge 1,580 ha. of farmland and mean the
relocation of 18,300 people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
