<HEADLINE> Chinese Students Studying Abroad Encouraged To Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China will create more favorable
conditions for Chinese students studying abroad to encourage them
to come back to China, Vice-Premier Li Lanqing told a visiting
group of 36 students studying abroad today.
</P>
<P>
Rapid economic growth and social development in China have
meant a great need for talented people and of students who have
gained a great deal of knowledge in the world, he said, and that
the nation's policy of sending students abroad, about 300,000 by
now, has proven fruitful over the past two decades. Many of them
have returned and have made contributions to the country.
</P>
<P>
Today's group of 36 students studying in 11 countries was
organized by the Ministry of Education last month. They have
finished a research project on environmental protection in the
city of Chongqing and in the Three Gorges Dam area. 
</P>
