<HEADLINE> 519 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Eastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police seized 519
kilograms of hashish in a recent operation against drug
trafficking in eastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News
agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Two suspects, named Riza Y. and Habip Y., were detained in
connection with the drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, police searched a mill at Mehmet Bayram
Street in Baskale town of Van province linking neighboring Iran
and found the hashish in 24 bags.
</P>
<P>
But the agency report did not say when the drugs were
confiscated.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs to Europe from the border
areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police seized
4.4 tonnes of heroin, which accounted for 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
</P>
