<HEADLINE> More Macao Holidaymakers Pass Through Zhuhai Checkpoint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 480,000 Macao residents
passed through the checkpoint between Macao and Zhuhai City in
southern China from October 1 to 5, according to sources from the
Zhuhai Customs.
</P>
<P>
The influx of passengers into the mainland of China is a result
of two major Chinese festivals: the National Day on October 1 and
the Mid-Autumn Festival which fell on October 5 this year. Many
people in Macao have relatives in the neighboring Pearl River
Delta area.
</P>
<P>
The number of passengers passing through the checkpoint is
about 15 percent more than that during the two festival period
last year.
</P>
<P>
On Monday morning, large groups of Macao people flocked to the
checkpoint in spite of drizzling. The customs opened a temporary
passage and a laptop computer was used to check in passengers.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 90,000 persons entered or left Zhuhai through the
checkpoint on Monday. 
</P>
