<HEADLINE> Singapore Resident Detained for Illegal Opium Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Customs officers at the Gaoqi
International Airport in Xiamen in east China have recently seized
1,757.4 grams (gross weight) of opium paste and 236.8 grams (gross
weight) of opium residue from an outgoing singapore resident.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore resident, Lin Fuquan, 66, was detained after he
was discovered to have hidden the opium paste and opium residue in
his suitcases on October 3 at Gaoqi Airport in Xiamen, capital of
Fujian Province, as he was about to board flight M1927 to
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Lin admitted he has been addicted to opium since the age of 22,
and said some of the seized opium was given to him by a friend in
Hui'an, a county in southeastern Fujian.
</P>
<P>
The case is now under further investigation. 
</P>
