<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Styrofoam Containers Banned Along China's Main Railways, Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China will ban the use of
plastic food containers along main railway lines and rivers and in
tourism regions to control the serious blight known as "white
pollution," an environmental official said here today.
</P>
<P>
A circular, jointly released recently by the State General
Administration of Environmental Protection, the ministries of
construction, railways and communications, and the National
Tourism Administration, prohibits the dumping of plastic
containers into and along rivers and lakes.
</P>
<P>
The local governments in provinces, municipalities and
autonomous regions have been asked to clean up plastic bags and
containers floating in the Yangtze River and Taihu Lake, and piled
up at tourism regions within three months.
</P>
<P>
And all the other refuse piles accumulating in the regions must
be treated within six months, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, tourism sites are required to provide enough garbage
cans, and garbage treatment stations are forbidden to be located
along rivers and lakes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
