<HEADLINE> Share Prices Drift Higher on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices drifted slightly
higher in very thin trading on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as
the benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) rebounded by 7.62 points
to 891.48 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover dropped to 72.53 million units valued at
110.40 million Singapore dollars (about 65.83 million U.S.
dollars). Losers led gainers by 96 to 84 while other 240 counters
were unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The larger block in transaction was a 5.19 million parcel of ST
Engg. SembCorp was the second most heavily traded stock with a
turnover of 4.65 million units. DUB F was next with 4.21 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F was the top gainer of the day with a rise of 30 cents to
6.40  Singapore dollars at close. Haw Par moved up 15 cents to
1.33 Singapore dollars. JurShip edged up 15 cents as well and
ended at 6.15 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 led the descents of the day with a
drop of 40 cents to 14.60 Singapore dollars. Venture w99 was the
second biggest loser with a slide of 28 cents to 3.80 Singapore
dollars. Elec&AMP;E shed off 50 cents to end at 4.50 Singapore
dollars. 
</P>
