<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Tuesday on strong buying from
local institutionals in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The market was boosted by the government's positive outlook on
the economy and also the National Bank's move to abolish limit on
loans to purchase properties and further cut in interest rates.
</P>
<P>
However, the market was unable to continue the uptrend and move
sideways in the afternoon on some profit taking.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index ended 3.99
percent or 14.35 points higher at 374.45, the all-share Emas Index
rose 3.38 points to 99.04, the Industrial Index added 21.77 points
to 741.32 and the Second Board Index gained 1.65 points to 91.76.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers by 497 to 86 while 98 counters were
unchanged and 235 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover rose to 146.262 million shares valued at
192.403 million ringgit (about 50.632 million U.S. dollars) from
79.096 million shares worth 98.951 million ringgit (about 26.039
million U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Main Board increased to 139.426 million shares
valued at 179.681 million ringgit (about 47.284 million U.S.
dollars) from Monday's 76.191 million shares worth 94.426 million
ringgit (about 24.848 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover rose to 6.836 million shares worth
12.722 million ringgit (about 3.347 million U.S. dollars) from
2.905 million shares valued at 4.525 million ringgit (about 1.19
million U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover increased to 9.302 million shares worth
4.654 million ringgit (about 1.224 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 3.770 million shares totaling 8.291 million ringgit
(about 2.181 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
