<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany's Jobless Total Down Below Four Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany's jobless total has dropped
for the first time in nearly two years below the psychological
four million mark, the German Federal Labor Office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Statistics released by the Nuremberg-based labor office showed
that a total of 3,965,400 people were out of work in September,
130,100 fewer than in August and 342,700 fewer than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate for September was down to 10.3 percent from
10.6 percent in August.
</P>
<P>
Improvement on the job market was reported both in western
Germany and in the east, with jobless people accounted for 8.8
percent of the active labor force in the west and 16.3 percent in
the east, the office said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
