<HEADLINE> China Concerned With Situation in Kosovo: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China is deeply concerned with
the current situation in Kosovo. Opposing use of force or threat
to use of force, and China hopes that the dialogue can be restored
as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remark at
today's regular press conference in reply to a reporter's question.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China is always opposed to the use of force or
threat to use of force in international relations, and that the
international community should comprehensively and realistically
evaluate the current situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The massive military conflicts in Kosovo had terminated
and the whole circumstances tended to ease, zhu said,
adding that the relevant sides had raised the new reference
on the political settlement of the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
"We hold that the sole measure for solving the Kosovo issue is
to pursue peaceful means through dialogues in the pretext of
respecting the sovereignty and territory integrity of Yugoslavia
and ensuring its national interests." he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said, the international community should follow
the norms of the international law and the principles and purposes
of the UN charter, and work steadfastly to contribute to the aim
of peace. 
</P>
