<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-06 09:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Pardons 2,300 Prisoners for War Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 6 (Xinhua) -- As part of the celebrations
marking Egypt's victory in the 1973 war against Israel, 2,300
prisoners have been released on parole on a presidential decree,
the Egyptian Gazette reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
President Hosni Mubarak has ordered the parole to the prisoners
who have served half of their sentence and demonstrated good
behavior, discipline and commitment to the prison rules.
</P>
<P>
Political prisoners will not, however, be freed. Prisoners who
committed violent crimes and arms smuggling were also excluded
from the amnesty.
</P>
<P>
The English-language daily newspaper quoted an official source
of Prison Department of the Interior Ministry as confirming that
fortunate prisoners would directly be sent to their families.
</P>
<P>
Leniency has been usually granted to prisoners on important
national or religious occasions in Egypt. This time is the 25th
anniversary of the October 6 war, when the Egyptian armed forces
took Israeli forces by surprise and crossed the Suez Canal, which
Israel had held since capturing Egypt's Sinai peninsula in the
1967 Arab-Israeli war.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptians were later pushed back, but Arab's first and
initial victory erased the shame of the 1967 defeat and allowed
Egypt to move toward peace with the Jewish state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981006.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-06 08:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Relatives to Visit Jordanian Prisoners in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Israel has allowed relatives of 14
of the Jordanian prisoners held in Israel to visit the inmates,
the semi-official Jordan Times reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Minister of Information Nasir Judeh as saying
that every prisoner's family can send two members to the Ashkelon
prison on October 20.
</P>
<P>
The visit was arranged by the Jordanian Embassy to Israel, the
paper said.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's consul to Israel will come back to accompany the
relatives to Israel, Judeh said.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, having a peace treaty signed with Israel in 1994,
enjoys the closest relationship with the Jewish state in the Arab
world.
</P>
<P>
Since the signing of the treaty, Israel has released 20
Jordanian prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Jordanian Ambassador to Israel Omar Rifai said
that in addition to the 14 Jordanians in the Ashkelon prison,
there are more Jordanians being held in Israeli jails for criminal
offenses. But he did not give the exact figures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
