<HEADLINE> Bus Collision Kills 18 Holiday-makers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, October 6 (Xinhua)-- Eighteen people died and 63 were
injured in a traffic accident last weekend in southwest China's
Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
On October 4, a tour bus bringing 86 holiday-makers back from
southern Guangdong Province fell into a 60-meter-deep ravine after
it collided head-on with another vehicle in Songtao Miao
Autonomous County.
</P>
<P>
Seventeen people were killed instantly and one died later. Five
of the original passengers had gotten off the bus earlier, while all
of the remaining passengers suffered injuries.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is still under investigation, local
sources said.
</P>
<P>
Most people had four days off for the National Day holiday on
October 1st.  
</P>
