<HEADLINE> Henan Prepares For Winter Planting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province, the nation's leading wheat producer, is busy preparing
to plant winter wheat.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to raise its summer grain output in 1999 to
23 billion kg, with wheat yields accounting for the bulk of total
output. Henan wheat currently accounts for more than 17 percent of
the total wheat output in China.
</P>
<P>
Local agricultural departments have stockpiled some 510 million
kg of wheat seed strains, 5.65 million tons of chemical
fertilizers, 220 million cu.m. of farmyard manure and 15,000 tons
of pesticides. Prices for related materials have dropped to the
lowest levels in a number of years.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Henan has introduced a unified seed distribution
system and is currently going all out to spread intensive
cultivation and interplanting techniques in order to further raise
output.
</P>
<P>
Some 3.49 million farmers in the province have attended
short-term training courses covering new techniques. 
</P>
