<HEADLINE> China Founds Sausage Casing Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Representatives from
European, North American and Chinese sausage casing enterprises
recently attended a ceremony marking the found of the China
Sausage Casing Association.
</P>
<P>
The association is expected to play a major role in
coordinating casing production, processing and exportation. It
will also help to strengthen the competitiveness of Chinese
products on the international market, according to one association
official.
</P>
<P>
China's sausage processing industry dates back well over a
century and currently leads the world in terms of both production
and exports of related products. The industry's annual export
volume accounts for close to a third of the world total.
</P>
<P>
Shunping County, located in north China's Hebei Province, is
the nation's major casing distribution center and export base. The
county's 146 casing plants, employing 20,000 people, export over
80 percent of their total production, and account for close to 20
percent of the nation's total exports of related products.  
</P>
</TEXT>
