<HEADLINE> Half of Romanian Gypsies are Illiterate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Nearly half the Gypsy
population in Romania cannot read or write, according to a report
issued Monday by the Ministry of National Education in Romania.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that only 4.5 percent of Romania's Gypsies
finish their high school education, while 44 percent of the male
Gypsy population and 59 percent of the female population of the
country receive no education at all.
</P>
<P>
At least one in two Gypsy children between the ages of 7-10 is
away from school and most of the gypsy children in their
pre-school years do not go to kindergarten, the report shows.
</P>
<P>
Gypsies tops the birth rate of Romania's ethnic peoples,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The Gypsies do not pay much attention to education for their
children, sociologists point out, while public discrimination
against Gypsies is another reason that keeps Gypsy children away
from school.
</P>
<P>
Romania has the largest Gypsy population in European
countries. A 1992 national census shows that Gypsies number
410,000 and make up 1.8 percent of Romania's total population.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
