<HEADLINE> Thai Government to Sell Off Rubber Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government plans to
sell off its rubber stock by the end of next month, the Bangkok
Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Agriculture Minister Somchai Sunthornwat was quoted as
saying the government's current rubber stock was less than 20,000
tons, down from 100,000 tons in January.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government has sold most of the rubber in stock to
China but in small batches so that it did not affect the market
much, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the Agriculture Ministry does not intend to keep stocks
after existing stocks are depleted to avoid price uncertainty.
</P>
<P>
"You don't know what will become of rubber prices or the baht
in a longer term. It is better to buy and sell quickly," Somchai
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
