<HEADLINE> Liaoning Accelerates Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, October 6 (Xinhua) -- China has abandoned the
practice of providing welfare-based housing for urbanites and the
construction of residential quarters is expected to emerge as a
new economic growth area in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to construct housing with a total
floor space of 50 million sq.m. over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
Half of the 31 million sq.m. currently under construction will
be completed by the end of this year. The province spent some
eight billion yuan completing 2.67 million sq.m. of housing during
the first eight months of the year.
</P>
<P>
The year's investments in housing construction will equal total
allocations for the previous three years combined.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has eliminated 56 fee items in order to make housing
affordable to local residents. 
