 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Liberation Army (PLA) will be cutting 500,000
personnel from its ranks during the next three years.
</P>
<P>
China's armed forces were reduced by one million personnel
during the 1980s. The current plan will be finished by 2000. By
then, China will have reduced the size of its armed forces by
seven million people during its 50-year history.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese scholars are working to make the nation's cities
cleaner and more beautiful by using the advanced technology they
have learned abroad.
</P>
<P>
