<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic on Monday strongly condemned the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) for its threat of armed strikes.
</P>
<P>
The president voiced the condemnation in a meeting with
U.S. special envoy Richard Holbrooke and U.S. ambassador to
Macedonia, Christopher Hill.
</P>
