<HEADLINE> Cuba Opens AIDS Telephone Inquiry Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 5 (Xinhua) -- Cuba's newly-opened telephone
service to give information on sexually-transmitted diseases has
received about 500 calls from the general public in the first
month, according to radio Habanera on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Most of the users were young males between 20 and 30, who
wanted specific information on human immune-deficiency virus (HIV).
</P>
