<HEADLINE> Technics Brings Prosperity to Tibetan Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- Tibetan farmers continue to
exhibit ever greater confidence in the use of technology to battle
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
Dawatserin, a farmer from Tingri County in Xigaze Prefecture,
the Tibet Autonomous Region, once invited Lamas to
chant sutras to protect against devastating hail and insect
infestations. Today, however, Dawatserin realizes that
technology provides answers to most related problems.
</P>
<P>
Technological applications helped raise the grain output on
Dawatserin's two hectares from less than 10,000 kg in previous
years to over 12,500 kg. in 1997, with his net income for the year
surpassing 12,000 yuan (1,400 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Local officials note that Tibetans continue to maintain strong
faith in their religion. However, they also point out that more
farmers are relying on science and technology to solve problems.
</P>
<P>
The local government has adopted a series of measures to
promote the use of advanced farming techniques, and offers
training courses for some 80,000 farmers each year. The effort has
also included the establishment of a group of pilot villages and
households focusing on the use of scientific and technological
findings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
