<HEADLINE> Poor Families in Indonesia increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of poor families in
Indonesia last month increased to 17.9 million from 17.5 million
in August, Antara News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the number of poor families was based on 23
economic and non-economic indicators, including the impact of the
economic crisis on mass layoffs and skyrocketing prices of staple
food, assistant to the coordinating minister for people's welfare
and poverty eradication A. Mongid said.
</P>
<P>
To promote the poor families' welfare, the government has
provided them with a working capital of 20,000 to 320,000 rupiah
(32 U.S. dollars) to run a business of their own, he said.
</P>
<P>
Now, there are an estimated 43.9 million families in Indonesia,
Mongid added. 
</P>
