<HEADLINE> Cohen to Visit Six Gulf Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 5 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary
William Cohen will visit six nations in the Gulf region to meet
with U.S. troops and discuss matters such as Iraq and Iran with
local officials, Pentagon officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will leave Wednesday for Bahrain. He also plans stops in
Qatar, the United Arab Emirates, Oman, Kuwait and Saudi Arabia
before returning to Washington on October 14.
</P>
<P>
A Pentagon official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said
that both "long-term and near-term" matters would be under
discussion.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will be expected to discuss Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein's lack of compliance with U.N. resolutions, and an
assessment from local leaders about their views toward Iran.
</P>
<P>
High on the agenda of his trip will also include such long-term
military matters as the potential for a regional theater missile
defense and possible agreements to smooth the insertion of U.S.
forces in the region during crisis.
</P>
<P>
Cohen plans to visit sailors on board the U.S. aircraft carrier
in the Gulf, the USS Abraham Lincoln, and to visit with American
forces currently detailed to Kuwait and Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
