<HEADLINE> Chinese Film Festival Opens in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 5 (Xinhua) -- About 200 people saw the film
"Chinese Wedding Customs" Monday afternoon, indicating the start
of the Chinese Film Festival in the country.
</P>
<P>
About 10 films, featuring the life style in China's Tibet
region, and the picturesque scenery of the Three Gorges etc. are
to be showed during the film festival, which is co-sponsored by
the Chinese Embassy in Mozambique and the Mozambican Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
Shao Guanfu, Chinese Ambassador to Mozambique said at the
opening ceremony of the film festival, that he was very glad at
the achievement Mozambique has made under the leadership of
President Joaquim Chissano.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique registered a 14 percent gross national product
growth with an inflation rate of only 5.8 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
Shao said that he wished the bilateral ties between China and
Mozambique could be pushed to a new stage.
</P>
<P>
Diolinda Quezumane, Secretary General of the Mozambican
friendship association said she finds the social and economical
achievement the Chinese people have made in recent years very
admiring and encouraging, adding that she was sure that those who
have suffered from the floods in China can overcome any
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
A private television station also held a Chinese TV feature
festival from September 26 to 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
